# Scenario: Load level 10 (test map), kill monster, rotate, loot.
# Verifies that combat dealt damage.
#
# Pattern note: this map has scripted help/info dialogs that fire on
# rotations / movements. We use the chain `do <ACTION>` + `do FIRE` +
# `await PLAYING` after each movement so that any dialog auto-dismisses
# and we're guaranteed back in PLAYING before the next step.
#
# args: --map levels/10_test_map --skip-intro --seed 1337

# Wait for map load
await PLAYING

# Attack the monster in front — 3 hits kill at this seed
do FIRE
do FIRE
do FIRE

# Killing the monster opens the souls reward dialog. Dismiss it.
await DIALOG
do FIRE
await PLAYING

# Rotate left, then absorb any auto-dialog that the rotation triggers.
do LEFT
do FIRE
do FIRE
await PLAYING

# Rotate right. After RIGHT, FIRE may either dismiss a help dialog OR
# (if facing the corpse) open LOOTING. Drain both possibilities then
# assert. We don't `await PLAYING` here because the script may legitimately
# end in LOOTING — checking the assertion is enough.
do RIGHT
do FIRE
do FIRE
do FIRE
do FIRE

expect damage_dealt > 0
